@NODE register "Register and support VideoLab!"

Nice that you thought about registering VideoLab. Please read the rest... I have
decided  to release VideoLab in this (yet unfinished) state to get an impression
about how many people are interested in this program. It  does  in  its  present
form  suit  my  personal  needs quite well, so I won't put any more work in this
project if there is no reason for it. So if you decide not to  register,  please
let me  know  why (@{"EMail" link author}  me!). I will treat this project as a test of how good
shareware works on the amiga. I've put quite some time into VideoLab and if  you
use  it  I  think  it's  worth a little donation. Further product's release form
depends on you!

There are different ways available to register VideoLab (This is to keep  prices
as low as possible!)

   Transfer modes:

   a) You may get your Keyfile via EMail  ( no extra costs )
      { This is if you cannot receive big EMails }

   b) You may get your Keyfile and the latest version of VideoLab via EMail
      (no additional costs)

   c) You may get the latest version of VideoLab and your keyfile vie Snail
      Mail. Additional costs are: DM 5 for disk and mailing costs!

   Additions:

   a) You may get an additional printed TeX-DVI manual. Additional costs
      again DM 5,-. Note that this is only possible if you chose
      point c) of the transfer modes.

   b) You may get an additionl TeX-DVI manual (unprinted, i.e. as file).
      Additional costs DM 2,-

The base registration fee is DM 15,- minimum or a more reasonable price!

Any addition which make snail mail necessary require transfermode  c).  That  is
currently only addition a)

To register fill out the @{"Registration Form" link RegForm/Main}  and  send  it  to  (I  won't  accept
registrations via EMail!) @{"me" link author}.

@ENDNODE

   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE PSvideo "PSVideo the Video-Cassette Database"

PSVideo is a Video-Cassette Database which supports all of the basic  functions,
needed  to  maintain a large amount of cassettes and keep track on how much time
is left on which cassette, as well as useful searching routines. If you  have  a
large collection of films and thought about a Video-Database, I would advise you
to have a look at PSVideo. Version 2.12 is currently available through aminet.

PSVideo is Copyright © by    Holger Papajewski & Jörg Stumpf

@ENDNODE

@NODE spech "SpecialHost"

SpecialHost is a tool used by the dvi-drivers of the  PasTeX  implementation  on
the  amiga.  You  may  add  backdrop  pictures  of  any format supported through
datatypes (OS versions 3.x +) and even postscript files. Datatype objects may be
modified  selecting  from  several  dither  methods  and  gama correction. For a
detailed explanation and examples, I ask you to take a look at  the  SpecialHost
documentation,  included  in the PasTeX distribution. For those of you who don't
use PasTeX: "I really recommend using this distribution", because it is:
   -  fast,
   -  for free,
   -  and complete.
You may get it from Aminet (I think this is without fonts!?) or from the Meeting
Pearls III CD-ROM (full distribution with complete source, docs, packages, LaTeX
2e and all drivers).

@ENDNODE

