If you have any problems using my programs, please drop me a line via  EMail  or
call  me  on  the above number and I will try to help! I am always interested in
getting nice mail (whatever it is!) or nice phone calls (please try not to  call
at midnight CET :).

VideoLab has been developed and tested on this system configuration:

   Amiga A4000 / 68EC030 / 68882
   2mb chip mem, 12 mb fast mem
   Piccolo-SD64 / 4mb graphics board
   Mitsumi FX-001 D CD-ROM
   2 HDs (Seagate and Maxtor)
   HP-Deskjet 500
   Hitachi 15mvx Multisync Monitor

_______

I am currently working on a program for maintaining and  graphically  presenting
measurement  data,  as  well  as  to perform statistical analysis on the data. I
would really like to make this program the best one available for the amiga. The
program  will  use  MUI3.3,  a fpu whenever possible and available and I plan to
include a script language which will allow the user to define new functions  and
access  all  internal  functions  as  well  as  other user defined ones. This is
because I don't have that much time (unfortunately) to do it all  myself.  I  am
still  gathering  suggestions  and  ideas,  but  at  the time it seems the first
version will support only 2D-dataplotting (3D is of course coming later)  and  a
simple  worksheet  to  manipulate the data. The plotting sceme will be much like
Origin on Windows systems (only better because of using  MUI).  Output  will  be
available on any system supported printer, as well as export to TeX,LaTeX, EPIC,
EEPIC and so on through the fig2dev program. If  you  have  any  suggestions  to
make,  please  let  me  know.  You  may of course support me through registering
VideoLab which is a test of shareware to me!

Thanks for support,

Chris





@ENDNODE

